    <p style="text-align: center;">Rick and JoAnne's NEW "Shack"</p>
    <div style="text-align: center;"><img src="file:///home/rick/n0njy_amateur_radio/images/Rick_JoAnne_Adventure.jpg"
        alt="" title="New Shack" style="width: 371px; height: 660px;"></div>
    <div style="text-align: center;"><br>
    </div>
    <div style="text-align: center;">Sailing Ketch Adventure</div>
    <div style="text-align: center;">a William Garden designed Transworld 41, a
      full keel, heavy displacement, ketch-rigged sailboat.</div>
    <div style="text-align: center;"><br>
    </div>
    <div style="text-align: center;">Displacement 16 tons, OAL= 50', Draft = 6',
      Beam = 13'</div>
    <div style="text-align: center;"><br>
    </div>
    <div style="text-align: center;">Antennas:&nbsp; VHF (Marine), HF insulated
      backstay (approx 35'), several wire antennas that can be hoisted in the
      rigging.</div>
    <div style="text-align: center;">Rigs: ICOM Marine radio, Icom IC-735,
      Yaseau VX7R, several marine handhelds and one Baofeng handheld.</div>
    <div style="text-align: center;"><br>
    </div>
    <div style="text-align: center;">Best part? Comes with two built in towers!
    </div>
